snippet: A Cairo court ordered the government to block access to YouTube for 30 days for carrying an anti-Islam film that set off deadly riots last year.
abstract: Egyptian court orders government to block access to Web site YouTube for carrying anti-Islam film that set off deadly riots in 2012, but ruling can be appealed and may not be enforced.
lead_paragraph: A Cairo court ordered the government to block access to YouTube for 30 days for carrying an anti-Islam film that set off deadly riots last year.

headline.seo: Egypt Court Orders Block on YouTube Over Anti-Islam Video
headline.main: Egypt Court Orders Block on YouTube Access
headline.print_headline: Egypt Court Seeks To Block YouTube
